</bibRefCitation>
), Chinese cress, shepherd's purse; collection locality was not stated by the author even though 
<collectingCountry box="[1190,1273,1028,1052]" name="Austria" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Austria</collectingCountry>
is presumed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,991,1485]" box="[197,929,1063,1088]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,441,1063,1088]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">General distribution</emphasis>
. Palaearctic (presumed to be only 
<collectingCountry box="[829,917,1063,1087]" name="Austria" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Austria</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,991,1485]" box="[197,1093,1099,1124]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,429,1099,1124]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Relation to the host</emphasis>
. This mite was associated with the deformation of flowers.
</paragraph>
